pr_title: Dagger DI implementation for BaseAimybox, fixes Aimybox multi-instantiation bug
pr_body:
> Under GSoC '23 ### Introduces Dagger Dependency Injection in the VoiceCommand module, for BaseAimybox class. Also fixes #986 **This PR does the following:** - [x] Transforms the `BaseAimybox` instance into an application context - [x] Ensures singularity for `Aimybox` instance - [x] Removes `BaseAimyboxViewModel`, as we do not use Aimybox UI components - [x] Establishes Single Responsibility Principle by assigning dependency jobs to Dagger - [x] Ensures a less coupled system
**Reasons:** 1. Due to use of `BaseAimyboxViewModel` viz. essentially for Aimybox UI components, we differed from the default application scoped implementation of Aimybox, which also resulted in #986 2. As fundamentally, there should only be **one running instance of Aimybox** in an application, using Dagger Singleton Scope we ensure this. 3. `BaseAimybox` provides functionalities that are used by many other UI elements (Activities/ Fragments), this results in high coupling between classes, with Dagger we address this.

pr_body:
## RTTG CI Workflow ⚙️

Mentions #3 

This PR contains the [Rasa Train Test Github Action](https://github.com/RasaHQ/rasa-train-test-gha) CI Workflow integration with the current assistant repository.
It uses [rasa-train-test-gha-enviroCar](https://github.com/devAyushDubey/rasa-train-test-gha-enviroCar), which is a custom GHA built on top of the existing [rasa-train-test-gha](https://github.com/RasaHQ/rasa-train-test-gha) 

The workflow has a single job and the following steps:
- **GitHub Checkout PR Step:**  It checks-out the head of the pull request i.e. last commit.
- **RTTG Action Step:**  Executes `rasa train` and `rasa test` commands, publishes the test report as a comment to the PR.
- **Output Test Report:**  Outputs the test report in the actions tab.
